il.ac.technion.nlp.nli.parser

Class NameValuesManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • il.ac.technion.nlp.nli.parser.NameValuesManager

  • public class NameValuesManager
extends java.lang.Object
    An object of this class defines the meaning of the NameValue objects created by the logic of il.ac.technion.nlp.nli.parser, and manages their creation such that no two NameValue objects with different ids would represent the same value. Note: we try to make the ids of the NameValue objects created by the logic informative for a human trying to debug the parser. But other than that when this class creates new NameValue objects it does not use the id string to store formal information (as done by Sempre's logic).
